# Documentation Standards

- Document public APIs, exported types, non-obvious invariants, and operational gotchas.
- Prefer concise rationale comments over comments that restate code.
- Update docs when changing behavior, contracts, setup, or public interfaces.

## Language Style
- JS/TS: JSDoc/TSDoc for exported functions, classes, and complex props.
- Python: Google-style docstrings for public modules/classes/functions.
- C/C++: Doxygen-style comments for public headers and ownership/lifetime rules.
- Java: Javadoc for public classes and methods, including checked exceptions and nullability expectations.
